---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import Link from "@components/ui/link.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import Container from "@components/container.astro";
import Sectionhead from "@components/sectionhead.astro";
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="Mitosisphere - Competitions">
  <style>
    :root {
      --primary-purple: #8b5cf6;
      --primary-blue: #3b82f6;
    }
    .link-primary {
      background-color: var(--primary-purple);
      color: white;
      transition: background-color 0.2s ease-in-out;
      border: 1px solid transparent;
    }
    .link-primary:hover {
      background-color: var(--primary-blue);
    }
    .glow-effect {
      position: absolute;
      top: 50%;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
      width: 400px;
      height: 400px;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3) 0%, rgba(139, 92, 246, 0) 70%);
      filter: blur(40px);
      z-index: 0;
    }
    .title-sheen {
       background: linear-gradient(100deg, #d1d5db 20%, #ffffff 50%, #d1d5db 80%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    }
  </style>

  <script id="MathJax-script" async src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js"></script>

  <div class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gray-900 text-white">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-purple-900/50 to-blue-900/50"></div>
    <div class="glow-effect"></div>
    <Container class="relative z-10">
      <main class="py-24 md:py-32 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold tracking-tight title-sheen">
          Competitions
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mt-6">
          We run two competitions, similar to the USABO Open and Semifinal Exams.
          Testing Info for the 2025 Season will come out later this year.
        </p>
        <Link
          href="https://forms.gle/7oaq31kiAhSstxwY6"
          target="_blank"
          class:list={["superround flex gap-1 items-center justify-center w-full md:w-[240px] mt-10 text-lg font-semibold link-primary mx-auto"]}
          rel="noopener">
          Sign Up!
        </Link>
      </main>
    </Container>
  </div>
  
  <div class="bg-blue-50/40 py-16 md:py-20">
    <Container>
      <main class="text-center">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-800">
          Rules & Information
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Open to high school students globally, the first round, the \(p+q=1\), will take place on <b>January 25th, 2025</b> online. Students will be able to take the exam any time between 12:00 AM and 11:59 PM EST. More information about the competition can be found in our rules document.
          </p>
          <Link
              href="/rules.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              class:list={["superround flex gap-1 items-center justify-center w-full md:w-[300px] mx-auto mt-10 font-semibold link-primary"]}
              rel="noopener">
              Rules Document
          </Link>
        </div>
      </main>
    </Container>
  </div>
  
  <div class="bg-white py-16 md:py-20">
    <Container class="space-y-16">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h3 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-800">
          \( p+q=1 \)
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The \(p+q=1\) is the first round of our competition, corresponding to the difficulty of the USABO Opens exam. The test consists of 50 questions to be completed in 50 minutes, including 45 multiple-choice and 5 multi-select questions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center">
        <h3 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-800">
          \( (p+q)^2=1 \)
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The \((p+q)^2=1\) is the second round, corresponding to the USABO Semifinals exam. The test consists of 120 questions in 120 minutes, including multiple-choice, multiple-true/false, and short free-response questions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </div>
</Layout>